How does the manufacturing year correlate with the resale price of Maruti vehicles?

In[5]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
df = pd.read_csv(r'cars24data.csv')

# Group by manufacturing year and calculate mean price
year_price = df.groupby('Manufacturing_year')['Price'].mean().reset_index()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(year_price['Manufacturing_year'], year_price['Price'], marker='o', linestyle='-', color='blue')
plt.title('Average Resale Price by Manufacturing Year')
plt.xlabel('Manufacturing Year')
plt.ylabel('Average Price (INR)')
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Average Resale Price by Manufacturing Year.png")
plt.show()

What is the average depreciation rate for Maruti vehicles based on age and mileage?

In[26]:
# Calculate year-over-year depreciation
year_price['Depreciation (%)'] = year_price['Price'].pct_change() * 100

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(year_price['Manufacturing_year'], year_price['Depreciation (%)'], marker='o', color='red')
plt.title('Annual Depreciation Rate')
plt.xlabel('Manufacturing Year')
plt.ylabel('Depreciation (%)')

How does ownership history interact with fuel type to influence resale prices?

In[37]:
ownership_fuel = pd.crosstab(df['Ownership'], df['Fuel type'], values=df['Price'], aggfunc='mean')

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
ownership_fuel.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
plt.title('Price by Ownership and Fuel Type')
plt.xlabel('Ownership')
plt.ylabel('Average Price (INR)')
plt.legend(title='Fuel Type')
plt.savefig("Price by Ownership and Fuel Type.png")
plt.show()
